      "visualKind": "shape",
      "title": "<h1>Job Stories for Dependency Management and Team Coordination</h1><p><em>Job stories are developed from structured user insights to inform user-centered design. These stories are synthesized to reflect the realities faced by Project Leads, particularly in managing dependencies, enhancing communication, and ensuring timely project completion.</em></p><h2>Job Story 1: Visualizing Task Dependencies</h2><p><em>When I</em> <strong>am under pressure to hit end-of-quarter deadlines</strong>, <em>I want to</em> <strong>visually see which tasks are preventing others from starting</strong>, <em>so I can</em> <strong>focus on high-level strategic work instead of chasing updates.</strong></p><h2>Job Story 2: Responding to Shifting Dependencies</h2><p><em>When I</em> <strong>am waiting for the Engineering team to finish their sprints before Design can start mocks</strong>, <em>I want to</em> <strong>easily reassign tasks when dependencies shift</strong>, <em>so I can</em> <strong>guarantee quarterly launch dates aren't missed.</strong></p><h2>Job Story 3: Efficient Communication</h2><p><em>When I</em> <strong>see my team is currently blocked by third-party vendors</strong>, <em>I want to</em> <strong>send direct notifications to the owners of blocking tasks</strong>, <em>so I can</em> <strong>stop manually checking in with team members.</strong></p><h2>Job Story 4: Clear Task Initiation</h2><p><em>When I</em> <strong>am managing multiple cross-functional projects under tight deadlines</strong>, <em>I want to</em> <strong>mark tasks clearly as \"Ready to Start\"</strong>, <em>so I can</em> <strong>ensure that the team knows exactly when they are unblocked and can get back to work effectively.</strong></p>"
    },
